== Roasted Sweet Potato and Carrots ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Put the sweet potato chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, sprinkle over half the @chermoula spice mix{0.75%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrots{2}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto another large baking tray. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, sprinkle over the remaining @chermoula spice mix{0.75%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

Roast on the middle shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Dressing ==

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @lentils{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Cut the @dried apricots{40%g} into small pieces.

Remove the @pistachios{12.5%g} from their shells and roughly chop.

In a large #bowl{}, add the @red wine vinegar{24%g}, @honey{30%g} and @olive oil{2.5%tbsp} for the dressing. Mix well to combine. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then set aside.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, add the lentils, dried apricots, roasted sweet potato and carrots to the dressing bowl.

Crumble in half the @Greek style salad cheese{100%g}, then toss to coat. Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

Just before serving, toss through the @baby leaf mix{50%g}.

> TIP: Don't do this too early or the leaves will go soggy.

Share the lentil salad between your #bowls{}.

Crumble over the remaining Greek style salad cheese and garnish with the pistachios to finish.

Enjoy!